  "text": "We conducted a case study based on a multimodal assessment through the acquisition of 118 objective psychophysiological and subjective self-report data. Our study was based on the 119 recently proposed \"juggling paradigm\", which purports that single studies in dyadic juggling 120 offer an epistemologically and methodologically valid platform to advance knowledge on the 121 coupling of peripheral (e.g., breathing and heart rate) and central mechanisms (e.g., hyperbrain 122 analysis) during interactive tasks (for a review see [CITATION_1] . Specifically, Filho et al.",
